I"Q<p>“Detection-Loophole-Free Test of Quantum Nonlocality, and Applications.” DOI: <a href="http://journals.aps.org/prl/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.130406">10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.130406</a>. We used a source of entangled photons to violate a Bell inequality free of the “fair-sampling” assumption. This work was selected as an Editor’s Suggestion and was <a href="http://physics.aps.org/synopsis-for/10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.130406">featured in Physics</a>. Read more about tests of nonlocality on our <a href="/QI/Photonics/research/#tests-of-nonlocality">Research page</a>.</p>
